NAME
    find_nonws - gives the index of first non-space
 
SYNOPSIS
    #include <acme.h>
    static inherit AcmeStrings;
    #include AcmeStringsInc

    varargs int find_nonws( string str, int start );
 
DESCRIPTION
    Returns the index of the first non-whitespace character in str,
    starting from position start.  This yeilds the same result as
    AcmeArray->anti_searcha( str, ' ', start ), but is faster.
 
EXAMPLE
    find_nonws("this is a test") -> 0
    find_nonws("     is a test") -> 5
 
SEE_ALSO
    anti_searcha(A)
 
LAST MODIFIED                               
